                            Broadmark Asset Management LLC (sub-advisor)                        


Broadmark Asset Management co-CEO and CIO Christopher Guptill and co-CEO Ricardo Cortez along with Salient chief investment strategist Ben Hunt oversee highly-adaptive long/short equity strategies that aim to lower the impact of equity volatility and preserve capital during down markets.





Christopher J. Guptill
Co-Chief Executive Officer, Chief Investment Officer & Portfolio Manager, Broadmark Asset Management			San Francisco





Ricardo Cortez, CIMA
Co-Chief Executive Officer, Broadmark Asset Management			San Francisco







                            Pacific Investment Management Company LLC (PIMCO) (sub-advisor)                        


Portfolio manager David Hammer, leads his New York-based team from PIMCO to sub-advise a long/short credit strategy for Salient. The team’s ability to short bonds and employ a variety of hedging techniques provides the strategy the opportunity to offer income and adaptability to portfolios.





David Hammer
Portfolio Manager, PIMCO			







                            Pictet Asset Management Limited. (PAM LTD) (sub-advisor)                        


Salient has partnered with Pictet Asset Management to sub-advise an international small cap companies strategy. Led by Bill Barker and Justin Hill, this seasoned United Kingdom-based team is dedicated to international small cap fundamental research and investing. Their in-depth style to this less-covered market provides the potential for better diversified portfolios.





Bill Barker
Head and Senior Investment Manager, Small Cap Equities Team, PAM Ltd.London 





Justin Hill
Senior Investment Manager, PAM Ltd.London 







                            Private Markets                        


Bill Enszer oversees Salient’s fund-of-funds portfolios and provides advisory services to the firm’s wealth management and family office platforms. Salient is an active investor in private equity, niche strategies and select co-investments, along with privately-held credit, real estate, energy and venture capital investments. Bill manages all aspects of the investment process, including manager research, sourcing, due diligence, portfolio construction, and portfolio monitoring.





Bill Enszer
Managing Director, Portfolio Management			Houston







                            Zarvona Energy (partner)                        


Founded in 2010 by energy industry veteran Kathryn S. MacAskie, Zarvona Energy, LLC (“Zarvona”) is a privately held independent oil & gas production and acquisition company headquartered in Houston, Texas. In 2011, Zarvona entered into a joint venture with Salient to lead an effort to acquire, further develop, and produce mature, long-lived oil and gas assets. Zarvona and its affiliates currently own interests in operated oil and gas fields in West Texas and western Oklahoma, and non-operated fields through Texas, Oklahoma, and New Mexico.





Kathryn S. MacAskie
President & CEO of Zarvona Energy			Houston





Robert M. MacAskie
Vice President of Acquisitions & Finance			Houston





Matthew Jurgens
Vice President of Operations			Houston







